Retrieve operation of resource: identifiers

200 OK
identifiers_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  
"identifiers": { LSP Identifiers

    
"tunnel-id": "integer", LSPO Tunnel ID

    
"te-lsp-id": "integer", TE LSP ID

    
"ext-tunnel-id": "integer", External Tunnel ID

    
"is-used": "boolean", LSP Identifier used flag

    
"sender": "string" Sender Address

  }
}

ERO - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-mpls-te-oper:mpls-pce/lsps/paths/ero/

Retrieve operation of resource: ero

200 OK
ero_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  
"ero": { Explicit Router Object

    
"subobject": [ 

      {
        
"local-address": "string", Address of the local address corresponding the\nadjacency SegmentID

        
"only-valid-mpls-label": "boolean", If this flag is true, SID has only MPLS label\nvalue. TC, S, and TTL fields are considered\ninvalid

        
"node-adjacency-id-exists": "boolean", If this flag is true, the bag contains\nNodeAdjacencyID information

        
"segment-id-value": "integer", Contains a SegmentID value in case SegmentID is\nvalid

        
"global": "boolean", Global

        
"missing-node-adjcency-id": "boolean", If this flag is true, ERO subobject does not\nhave NodeAdjacencyID

        
"ipv4-prefix-len": "integer", IPv4 Address Prefix Length

        
"missing-segment-id": "boolean", If this flag is true, ERO subobject does not\nhave SegmentID

        
"segment-id-exists": "boolean", If this field is true, the bag contains\nSegmentID value

        
"ipv4-address": "string", IPv4 address

        
"remote-address": "string", Address of the remote address corresponding the\nadjacency SegmentID

        
"subobj-type": "integer", Route Subobject Type

        
"complete-mpls-label-entry": "boolean", If this flag is true, all fields of MPLS labe\nentry are valid

        
"strict": "boolean", Strict

        
"segment-id-type": "string", Segment ID Type

        
"mpls-label": "integer", MPLS Label in case Segment ID type is MPLS

        
"node-id": "string" Address of the node corresponding the node\nSegmentID

      }
    ],
    
"cost": "integer", Cost

    
"is-used": "boolean" Route Object used flag

  
"address": [ 

    {,
    
"entry": "string"  

      }
    ]
  }
}
